<dec f='include/pulse/format.h' l='141' type='int pa_format_info_to_sample_spec(pa_format_info * f, pa_sample_spec * ss, pa_channel_map * map)'/>
<doc f='include/pulse/format.h' l='136'>/** Utility function to generate a \a pa_sample_spec and \a pa_channel_map corresponding to a given \a pa_format_info. The
 * conversion for PCM formats is straight-forward. For non-PCM formats, if there is a fixed size-time conversion (i.e. all
 * IEC61937-encapsulated formats), a &quot;fake&quot; sample spec whose size-time conversion corresponds to this format is provided and
 * the channel map argument is ignored. For formats with variable size-time conversion, this function will fail. Returns a
 * negative integer if conversion failed and 0 on success. \since 2.0 */</doc>
